# Credits

This page is intended to give credit other people's contributions that made this website possible.

## Figma Library

This idea started when I discovered a downloadable figma file on [github](https://github.com/skumando/figma-patterns) by [Chris Orebaugh](http://www.chrisorebaugh.com/). , containing lots of patterns intended to be used as background-images. I published them as a [Figma Library](https://www.figma.com/community/file/978689698060140147) to the community. I needed them on my own project but I quickly realized that I would need them to be not-background-images in my document, so I could easily [change their colors with custom properties](https://helloyes.dev/blog/2021/very-simple-patterns-with-svg/).

I eventually started to hand-code them. This website serves as a vault, a respository for these patterns, so I can easily copy and paste them into my projects.

